article.headline: Jacobs leads Eagles with 26 points
article.linkText: Boston College gives coach Inglese 300th victory
article.story:
CHESTNUT HILL, Massachusetts (Ticker) -- Amber Jacobs scored 
a season-high 26 points and coach Cathy Inglese nailed down her
300th career win as No. 20 Boston College defeated
UNC-Greensboro, 84-53.

Jacobs shot 7-for-10 from the floor, including 4-for-6 from long
range, and supplied seven assists. The senior guard also
drained all eight of her free throws as the Eagles (9-1) went
19-for-21 from the line.

Brooke Queenan produced 17 points and eight rebounds for Boston
College, which put together a 21-3 run en route to a 51-27 lead
at the half. The Eagles, who are off to their best start in
school history, opened the second half on a 15-5 run.

Lisa Macchia contributed 15 points and three steals for Boston
College, which has won its last two games by an average of 38
points since suffering a one-point, overtime loss to George
Washington December 10.

Amanda Eaton scored 18 points and Jasmine Byrd added 10 for the
Spartans (2-8), who were outscored in the paint, 32-14.
